    "updated_at": "2025-03-14T18:59:45Z",
    "body": "You can `cargo install starship`, at least on Debian-testing/riscv:\n\n```\nplough:~ $ uname -a\nLinux plough 5.10.113-scw1 #1 SMP PREEMPT Fri Jul 12 15:31:22 UTC 2024 riscv64 GNU/Linux\nplough:~ $ starship explain\n\n Here's a breakdown of your prompt:\n \"david@\" (<1ms)   -  The active user's username\n \"plough:\" (<1ms)  -  The system hostname\n \"~ \" (<1ms)       -  The current working directory\n \"$ \" (<1ms)       -  A character (usually an arrow) beside where the text is entered in your terminal\n```\n\nand _some_ things work, but it seems that either starship or (more likely, I think) one of its dependencies is a bit dodgy, because:\n\n```\nplough:~/dir-that-is-a-git-repo $ starship explain\nIllegal instruction\n```\n\nIf any of the devs want to look into that I'm happy to set them up with an account.",
