    "updated_at": "2026-03-22T19:00:19Z",
    "body": "Starship 1.24.2 builds on native riscv64 hardware with no source changes needed (BananaPi F3, SpacemiT K1, rv64gc). Both gnu and musl targets should work.\n\nNative riscv64 GitHub Actions runners are now available through the RISE Project (ubuntu-24.04-riscv), free for open source projects. This avoids cross-compilation entirely. To enable: install the RISE runners GitHub App (https://github.com/apps/rise-risc-v-runners).\n\nI can put together a PR adding riscv64gc-unknown-linux-gnu to the release matrix if that would help move this forward.",
